doc.field: Description: Plastic bag of many charms and chains labeled by MR: Charms A(52) and B(11) 4/11/95. Two silver necklace chains, one silver bracelet. One silver bracelet with charms. Loose silver charms: four smiling skull charms; cow, windmill, raccoon with New Orleans tag, chicken, elephant, elk, giraffe, kangaroo, jackalope, boar with New Orleans tags, swinging monkey, tiger with New Orleans tag, fly, bag of money with Cascade Caverns tag, crawling baby, pair of dice, handgun with New Mexico tag, kinetic clown, hand in handcuff, anchor, sphinx, man wrapped around lamppost, hut and palm tree, truck, ship, aircraft carrier, St. Hubert medallion, Mickey Mouse, Minnie Mouse, Donald Duck, Goofy, three see no evil monkeys in bag. Loose silver charm tags: two New York World's Fair flags, New York flag, New Mexico, Trees of Mystery, Grand Canyon, Colorado. Copper kneeling man charm. Three empty gun shells. Flattened coin ""Marsh's Free Museum Long Beach with image of human-crocodile hybrid named Jake. Blank paper tag. Silver jewelry ring. Earring ear wire.
Series XIII: Objects and Artifacts >> Subseries B: The "Magic Box" >> Bag of Charms and Chains
